        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks JvH for his address [to the Philosophical Institute of Canterbury], his Geological Report [<hi rend="italic">Topographical and geological exploration of the western districts of the Nelson province, New Zealand</hi> (1861)],</p>  
<p>and for the "honourable" notice of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p> 
            <p>CD especially interested in JvH’s facts on the old glacial period.</p> 
<p>Asks about fossil remains [of supposed living mammalia] which CD thinks may be like "the Solenhofen bird-creature" [<hi rend="italic">Archaeopteryx</hi>].</p> 
            <p>Urges the recording of rate and manner of spreading of European weeds and plants and observation on which native plants "most fail".</p>
        </abstract>
